The paper deals with signal reconstruction from quantized random projections, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The use of Gaussian random frames and measurements is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses compressed sensing (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) techniques for signal reconstruction.
